SUMMARY—Revises the Nevada Fair Housing Law.
(BDR 10-460)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: No.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to housing; prohibiting a landlord from refusing to
rent a dwelling to a corporation that rents a dwelling on
behalf of a person with a disability solely because the
corporation provides assistance in obtaining housing to a
person with a disability; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law sets forth the Nevada Fair Housing Law which prohibits certain
2 discriminatory housing practices. (NRS 118.010-118.120) The Nevada Fair
3 Housing Law prohibits a person from refusing to sell or rent a dwelling to any
4 person on the basis of race, religious creed, color, national origin, disability, sexual
5 orientation, gender identity or expression, ancestry, familial status or sex. (NRS
6 118.100) Section 1 of this bill prohibits a landlord from refusing to rent or
7 negotiate for the rental of, or otherwise make unavailable or deny, a dwelling to a
8 corporation that rents a dwelling on behalf of a person with a disability solely
9 because the corporation provides assistance in obtaining housing to a person with a
10 disability. Section 1 requires a landlord to submit a written explanation of the
11 reasons the landlord denied an application to rent a dwelling submitted by such a
12 corporation to the corporation, the Aging and Disability Services Division of the
13 Department of Health and Human Services and the Office of the Ombudsman for
14 Owners in Common-Interest Communities and Condominium Hotels within 7 days
15 after the landlord denies such an application.
16 Section 2 of this bill applies the definitions in existing law governing the
17 Nevada Fair Housing Law to the provisions of section 1.
